The completion of James Rodriguez £60million transfer to Real Madrid completes the most frightening, and most expensive trio in world football.

In fact, when added to Gareth Bale and Cristiano Ronaldo's £86m and £80m deals, Real can now boast an attacking midfield that costs more than the transfer spend of Dutch giants Ajax in their entire 114-year history.

The four-time European Cup winners have spent just £183million on transfers - £43million less than the Real cash splashed out on the expensively-assembled trio.

