While Ajax's record signing was £13million Miralem Sulejmani, only Marcelo (£5m, signed aged 19), Raphael Varane (£8m, aged 18), Daniel Carvajal (£4m, aged 21) and Diego Lopes (£3m) cost less from next year's expected Real starting XI

Madrid have a history of expensive signings from the Galactico era, but the class of 2014 put even the likes of Zinedine Zidane, David Beckham and Luis Figo to shame.

Even Barcelona, who added £75million Luis Suarez to the £71million purchase of Neymar this summer, don't come close - although the disparity is helped by the inclusion of La Masia product Lionel Messi, whose transfer fee in today's market could help Barca make up the £80million gap.

And so as Rodriguez dons a Real shirt for the first time on Tuesday evening, he completes a staggering £226million line-up that will leave the money men as opened-mouthed as the defenders who will likely be chasing shadows in La Liga next season.

